An Umuahia Magistrate Court has remanded one Nkemjika Lawrence (m) in prison custody for allegedly raping a teenager (names withheld) under threat in her parents house. Lawrence was said to had late last year in Umuelem Amakama, Ubakala in Umuahia South Magisterial District, gained entery forcefully into the house and committed the offence. The suspect was equally said to had at the sametime stolen an Andriod phone whose valued is yet to be determined belonging to one of the relations of the teenager. The presiding magistrate, His Worship, Mr. Idika Kalu said the suspect committed an offence punishable under sections 358 and 390 (a) of the Criminal Code vol. 3 Laws of Abia state. Kalu said his court lacked jurisdiction over the matter and therefore ordered the original case file be transmitted to the state Director of Public Prosecution (DPP) for further investigations and advice. However, he ordered the remand of the suspect at Umuahia Correctional Home/Facility, Afara until 30 March 2020 for report of compliance. In another development, an 18-year old boy has been arraigned before another magistrate court in the state capital, Umuahia for unlawful
possession of a locally made double barrel gun. Arraigning the suspect before His Worship, Mr. Nnaemeka Orji, the police prosecutor alleged that he was arrested at Waterside Aba in Aba South Magisterial District. The suspect is acussed of committing an offence punishable under section 3 (1) of the Robbery and Firearms (Special Provision) Act. cap R11 Law of the Federation of Nigeria 2004 as applicable in the state.